`,t.jsx(e.p,{children:"When a machine broke down or a raw material shipment came in late, someone had to open all three files, cross-reference operator shift schedules, check machine maintenance windows, and redistribute work by hand. On a good day this took 90 minutes. On a bad day, the 6 AM reconciliation ran until noon — and production had already started on the wrong schedule."}),`
